and unrelated render paths.\n- Required outputs:\n  - one typed immutable capability source used by the actual production SDL GPU path and the public `RenderingServer` binding;\n  - no duplicated hand-maintained feature arrays for the same selected presenter;\n  - production `RuntimeHost` evidence without direct test calls to `SetBackend`.\n- Required commands:\n  - `dotnet build src/Electron2D/Electron2D.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`\n  - existing focused `RuntimeHostTests.RuntimeFramePresenterUsesSdlRendererFallbackWhenGpuPresenterCreationFails`\n  - existing focused `RenderingServerBackendTests`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- update api-manifest --check`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- update docs --check`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify licenses`\n  - `git diff --check`\n- External audit: not required by default; require it only if public feature values, signatures or profile semantics change.\n\n### Internal substrate acceptance contract\n\n- Input boundary: capabilities of the presenter actually selected by `RuntimeFramePresenter` for SDL GPU or SDL Renderer.\n- Selection invariant: `RenderingServer.CurrentProfile` and `HasFeature` observe the same immutable capability source as the active production presenter.\n- Failure policy: a presenter/backend capability mismatch fails focused production-selection tests instead of silently publishing a second feature list.\n- Consumer boundary: `RuntimeHost` selection, public `RenderingServer` binding and backend diagnostics agree without direct test-only backend replacement.\n- Regression boundary: all six not-yet-wired features remain `false`; fallback still selects `Compatibility`.\n\n### Самодостаточное описание\n\n`StandardRenderingBackend` и `SdlGpuRenderingBackend` сейчас содержат одинаковые ручные feature arrays, а `RuntimeFramePresenter` после создания GPU presenter привязывает к публичному facade новый `StandardRenderingBackend`, а не capability